<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 12 at 1:18PM ADT  by NWS San Juan</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Lajas, Cabo Rojo,
southwestern San German and Hormigueros Municipalities through 145 PM
AST...
At 1217 PM AST, a strong thunderstorm was over Puerto Real, or near
Cabo Rojo, moving west around 20 mph.
HAZARD...Frequent lightning and heavy rain.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Lightning is one of nature`s leading killers. If you can
hear thunder, you are close enough to be struck by
lightning. Heavy rain may cause temporary street flooding
especially in poor drainage areas.
Locations impacted include...
Hormigueros, Cabo Rojo, Lajas, Puerto Real, Monte Grande, Pole Ojea,
Boqueron, Sabana Eneas and Betances.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. Electrical
appliances should not be used unless in an emergency. Motorists
should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.</instruction>
